revision.text:
The '''Albright-Gambari Commission''', formally known as the '''Commission on Global Security, Justice & Governance''', is a commission that was formed by the [[Hague Institute for Global Justice]] and the [[Stimson Center]] to consider new frameworks for collective action on issues such as [[state fragility]], [[climate change]], and the [[cyber‐economy]]. It is co-chaired by former U.S. Secretary of State [[Madeleine Albright]] and former Nigerian Foreign Minister and UN Under-Secretary-General Professor [[Ibrahim A. Gambari]].<ref>http://www.globalsecurityjusticegovernance.org/about/</ref> {{politics-stub}}

