{{BLP sources|date=March 2012}} {{Infobox scientist |name = Andrew Carnie |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1969|4|19}} |birth_place = [[Calgary|Calgary, Alberta]] |death_date = |death_place = |residence = [[Tucson, Arizona]] |citizenship = |nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]] |ethnicity = |field = [[Linguistics]] |work_institutions = |alma_mater = [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] |doctoral_advisor = [[Kenneth Hale]] |doctoral_students = |known_for = |influences =[[Noam Chomsky]] |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Andrew Carnie''' (born April 19, 1969) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[professor]] of [[linguistics]] at the [[University of Arizona]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=ADSB&s_site=azstarnet&f_site=azstarnet&f_sitename=Arizona+Daily+Star%2C+The+%28AZ%29&p_multi=ADSB&p_theme=gannett&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=13019AACCA973A38&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title=Outstanding UA faculty members are recognized|date=May 21, 2010|work=Arizona Daily Star|accessdate=8 July 2012}}</ref> He is the author or coauthor of eight books and has papers published on formal [[syntax|syntactic theory]] and on linguistic aspects of [[Scottish Gaelic]] and the [[Irish language]]. He was born in [[Calgary|Calgary, Alberta]]. He is also a teacher of Balkan and [[international folk dance]]. In 2009, he was named as one of the Linguist List's Linguist of the Day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://linguistlist.org/studentportal/linguists/carnie.cfm|title=Andrew Carnie, University of Arizona|website=linguistlist.org|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref> Since 2010, he has worked as the faculty director of the University of Arizona's Graduate Interdisciplinary Programs. In August 2012, he was appointed interim Dean of the graduate college.
==Linguistics==
The bulk of Carnie's research has been in the field of [[syntax]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dingo.sbs.arizona.edu/~carnie/vita/PDF/vita.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-03-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323142847/http://dingo.sbs.arizona.edu/~carnie/vita/PDF/vita.pdf |archivedate=2017-03-23 |df= }}</ref>
