{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Expert shopping''' is the practice of finding an [[Expert|authority]] on a given subject whose professional opinion is skewed toward the answer that the searching party already prefers. This is commonplace in the [[news media]], [[politic]]s, and [[business]], though can be found in all walks of life.

Another well-known use is in [[lawsuit]]s, when an [[expert witness]] can be paid to testify in favor of one side of the case. In this case, the expert witnesses on each side may have totally different opinions.{{DEFAULTSORT:Expert Shopping}}
